// Circle equation: F(x,y) = x² + y² - r²
// Midpoint between E(x+1,y) and SE(x+1,y-1) is M(x+1, y-0.5)

// At point k, pk = F(xk+1, yk-0.5)
// = (xk+1)² + (yk-0.5)² - r²

// If pk < 0 (midpoint inside), next pixel is E(xk+1, yk)
// pk+1 = F(xk+2, yk-0.5)
// = (xk+2)² + (yk-0.5)² - r²
// = pk + 2*xk+1 + 1

// If pk ≥ 0 (midpoint outside), next pixel is SE(xk+1, yk-1)
// pk+1 = F(xk+2, yk-1.5)
// = (xk+2)² + (yk-1.5)² - r²
// = pk + 2*xk+1 - 2*yk + 1
